# Testing Conventions

## Framework
- **Test runner**: Vitest with `globals: true`
- **DOM rendering**: React Testing Library (`@testing-library/react`)
- **Assertions**: `@testing-library/jest-dom` (available via `vitest.setup.ts`)

## Coverage Requirements
100% across statements, branches, functions, and lines — enforced via Vitest thresholds.

## File Structure
```
__tests__/
  components/Hero.test.tsx     ← mirrors components/Hero.tsx
  components/Footer.test.tsx
  lib/blog.test.ts             ← mirrors lib/blog.ts
  lib/constants.test.ts
  app/page.test.tsx
  app/blog/page.test.tsx
```

## Pre-mocked in vitest.setup.ts
- `framer-motion` → passthrough div/span renders (no animation in tests)
- `next/font/google` → returns `{ className: 'mock-...' }`
- `next/navigation` → stub router, pathname

## Example Test Pattern
```tsx
import { render, screen } from '@testing-library/react'
import { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest'
import { Footer } from '@/components/Footer'

describe('Footer', () => {
  it('renders the owner name', () => {
    render(<Footer />)
    expect(screen.getByText(/Himanshu Shrivastava/i)).toBeInTheDocument()
  })

  it('renders GitHub link', () => {
    render(<Footer />)
    const link = screen.getByRole('link', { name: /github/i })
    expect(link).toHaveAttribute('href', expect.stringContaining('github.com'))
  })
})
```

## Query Priority (best → worst)
1. `screen.getByRole` — most accessible, preferred
2. `screen.getByLabelText` — for form fields
3. `screen.getByText` — for visible text
4. `screen.getByAltText` — for images
5. `screen.getByTestId` — last resort only

## Mocking MDX (for blog pages)
```tsx
vi.mock('next-mdx-remote/rsc', () => ({
  MDXRemote: ({ source }: { source: string }) => <div data-testid="mdx">{source}</div>
}))
```

## Rules
- Test what users see/do — not internal state or implementation
- One `describe` per component, multiple `it` blocks
- Test all conditional branches (affects coverage)
- Test accessibility: check roles, labels, and keyboard interactions
